[34m│[0m ## Business Logic Errors Attack Playbook                                     [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m                                                                              [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m > **IMPORTANT:** All techniques in this playbook are EXAMPLES that must be   [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m ADAPTED for your specific target. Replace placeholders like `{PARAMETER}`,   [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m `{VALUE}`, `{ENDPOINT}` with actual values. Adapt techniques based on:       [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m > - Target application's business logic and workflows                        [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m > - Available parameters and endpoints                                       [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m > - Authentication and authorization mechanisms                              [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m > - Observed application behavior                                            [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m                                                                              [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m > Business logic errors exploit the application's intended functionality in  [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m unintended ways, rather than code vulnerabilities like SQL injection or XSS. [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m                                                                              [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m ### Core Testing Methodology                                                 [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m                                                                              [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m **Review Feature Testing:**                                                  [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m - Post product review as verified reviewer without purchasing                [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m - Provide rating outside scale (0, 6, negative in 1-5 scale)                 [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m - Post multiple ratings for same product (race condition test)               [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m - Check file upload field allows all extensions                              [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m - Post reviews impersonating other users                                     [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m - Test CSRF on review feature (often unprotected)                            [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m                                                                              [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m **Discount Code Feature Testing:**                                           [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m - Apply same discount code multiple times (reusability)                      [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m - Test race conditions: apply same unique code simultaneously from two       [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m accounts                                                                     [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m - Mass Assignment/HTTP Parameter Pollution: apply multiple codes when only   [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m one expected                                                                 [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m - Test XSS/SQLi on discount code input                                       [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m - Apply discount codes to non-discounted items via server-side request       [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m manipulation                                                                 [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m                                                                              [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m **Delivery Fee Manipulation:**                                               [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m - Test negative values for delivery charges                                  [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m - Modify parameters to activate free delivery                                [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m                                                                              [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m **Currency Arbitrage:**                                                      [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m - Pay in one currency (USD), request refund in another (EUR)                 [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m - Exploit conversion rate differences for profit                             [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m                                                                              [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m **Premium Feature Exploitation:**                                            [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m - Access premium-only sections/endpoints without subscription                [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m - Purchase premium, cancel, check if still accessible after refund           [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m - Look for true/false values in requests/responses validating premium access [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m - Use Burp Match & Replace to alter premium validation values                [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m - Review cookies/localStorage for premium access variables                   [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m                                                                              [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m **Refund Feature Exploitation:**                                             [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m - Purchase product, request refund, check if product remains accessible      [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m - Test currency arbitrage opportunities                                      [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m - Submit multiple cancellation requests for subscription (multiple refunds)  [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m                                                                              [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m **Cart/Wishlist Exploitation:**                                              [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m - Add products in negative quantities with other products to balance total   [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m - Add more product than available                                            [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m - Move product from your wishlist/cart to another user's cart                [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m - Remove products from other users' carts                                    [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m                                                                              [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m **Thread Comment Testing:**                                                  [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m - Check comment limit on threads                                             [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m - If one comment per user, test race conditions for multiple comments        [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m - If verified/privileged users can comment, mimic parameters                 [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m - Post comments impersonating other users                                    [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m                                                                              [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m **Rounding Error Exploitation:**                                             [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m - Test transfers below minimum precision (e.g., 0.000000005 XBT)             [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m - Exploit rounding differences between sender (rounds down) and receiver     [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m (rounds up)                                                                  [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m - Automate process if no rate limit/OTP/fraud detection                      [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m                                                                              [34m│[0m
